<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1015,1148]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Comments: A pelagic species rarely found in coastal waters; recorded from Brazilian waters (
<bibRefCitation author="Kirkaldy &amp; Torre-Bueno" firstAuthor="Kirkaldy" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="173 - 213" refId="ref38973" refString="Kirkaldy, G. W. &amp; Torre-Bueno, J. R. de la (1909) A catalogue of American aquatic and semi aquatic Hemiptera. Proceedings of the Entomological Society of Washington, 10, 173 - 213." type="journal article" year="1909">Kirkaldy &amp; Torre-Bueno 1909</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Herring" box="[371,524,1124,1148]" firstAuthor="Herring" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="223 - 305" refId="ref37993" refString="Herring, J. L. (1961) The genus Halobates (Hemiptera: Gerridae). Pacific Insects, 3, 223 - 305." type="journal article" year="1961">Herring 1961</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Cheng" box="[536,675,1124,1148]" firstAuthor="Cheng" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="111 - 135" refId="ref34697" refString="Cheng, L. (1985) Biology of Halobates (Heteroptera: Gerridae). Annual Review of Entomology, 30, 111 - 135." type="journal article" year="1985">Cheng 1985</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Andersen &amp; Cheng" box="[687,969,1124,1148]" firstAuthor="Andersen" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="119 - 180" refId="ref33869" refString="Andersen, N. M. &amp; Cheng, L. (2004) The marine insect Halobates (Heteroptera: Gerridae): biology, adaptations, distribution and phylogeny. Oceanography and Marine Biology, an Annual Review, 42, 119 - 180." type="journal article" year="2004">Andersen &amp; Cheng 2004</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Dias &amp; Lopes" box="[981,1204,1124,1148]" firstAuthor="Dias" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="67 - 73" refId="ref35736" refString="Dias, J. F. &amp; Lopes, C. L. (2009) Occurrence, distribution and abundance of Halobates micans Eschscholtz, 1822 (Heteroptera, Gerridae) along the Southeastern Brazilian Coast. Brazilian Journal of Biology, 69, 67 - 73." type="journal article" year="2009">Dias &amp; Lopes 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
