</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,647,1303,1328]" box="[151,647,1303,1328]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<taxonomicName authority="Bergroth, 1892" authorityName="Bergroth" authorityYear="1892" box="[151,506,1303,1328]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Rheumatobates" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,330,1303,1328]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Rheumatobates</emphasis>
Bergroth, 1892
</taxonomicName>
(10 species)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,1375,1544]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Comments: 
<taxonomicName authority="Drake &amp; Harris, 1944" authorityName="Drake &amp; Harris" authorityYear="1944" box="[294,867,1375,1400]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Rheumatobates" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carvalhoi">
<emphasis box="[294,587,1376,1400]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Rheumatobates carvalhoi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Drake &amp; Harris" box="[602,867,1375,1399]" firstAuthor="Drake" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="269 - 272" refId="ref36955" refString="Drake, C. J. &amp; Harris, H. M. (1944) A new Rheumatobates from Brazil, with a note on R imitator (Uhler) (Hemipt. Gerridae). Revista de Entomologia, 15, 269 - 272." type="journal article" year="1944">Drake &amp; Harris, 1944</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
was described from southeastern 
<collectingCountry box="[1283,1351,1375,1399]" name="Brazil" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(MG). According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Polhemus and Manzano" box="[305,657,1412,1436]" firstAuthor="Polhemus" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="302 - 320" refId="ref41948" refString="Polhemus, J. T. &amp; Manzano, M. R. (1992) Marine Heteroptera of the Eastern Tropical Pacific (Gelastocoridae, Gerridae, Mesoveliidae, Saldidae, Veliidae). In: Quintero, D. &amp; Aiello, A. (eds.), Insects of Panama and Mesoamerica. Selected Studies. Oxford University Press, Oxford, New York, Tokyo, pp. 302 - 320." type="book chapter" year="1992">Polhemus and Manzano (1992)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Drake &amp; Harris" authorityYear="1944" box="[669,807,1412,1436]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Rheumatobates" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carvalhoi">
<emphasis box="[669,807,1412,1436]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">R. carvalhoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only member of the 
<emphasis box="[1108,1225,1413,1436]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">aestuarius</emphasis>
group of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Bergroth" authorityYear="1892" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Rheumatobates" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Rheumatobates</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to occur outside of the Eastern Tropical Pacific. Based on the ecology, taxonomy, and geographical distribution of the species of the group, those authors mentioned having serious doubts concerning the validity of the locality data of the type-series of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Drake &amp; Harris" authorityYear="1944" box="[522,659,1520,1544]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Rheumatobates" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carvalhoi">
<emphasis box="[522,659,1520,1544]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">R. carvalhoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Being so, the Brazilian record of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Drake &amp; Harris" authorityYear="1944" box="[1042,1179,1520,1544]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Rheumatobates" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="carvalhoi">
<emphasis box="[1042,1179,1520,1544]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">R. carvalhoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is not considered here.
</paragraph>
